The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Subramaniam joins support staff

LOKENDRA PRATAP SAHI

Colombo: Tata Consultancy Services Shiva Subramaniam, who worked with the Team India probables on the opening day of the final camp in Bangalore, has joined Rahul Dravid and Co. in Dambulla. 

Subramaniam, a master in the Edward de Bono line of lateral thinking, arrived on Thursday and will be part of the support staff for a few days. 

His involvement is at coach Greg Chappells behest. 

As of now, Im around for a couple of days... Perhaps, till the first two matches of the tri-series, Subramaniam told The Telegraph, when contacted at the team hotel in Dambulla. 

Indias opening match, on Saturday, is against hosts Sri Lanka. On Sunday, Dravids men cross swords with the West Indies. 




